---
layout: project
title: Download - Cache Stores
---

.row-fluid
  .span9

    %ul.breadcrumb
      %li
        %a{:href => "/download.html"} Downloads
        %span.divider /
      %li.active Hot Rod Clients

    %h1 Hot Rod Clients
    .row-fluid
      %table.table.table-striped
        %tbody
          -# Loops through all of the hotrod clients listed in ispn.yml
          - site.ispn.hotrod.each do |client_name, client_info|
            %tr
              %td
                %h3 #{client_info.title}
                %p
                  = partial(client_info.text)
              %td
                -# If the client is a Java client, then display download links + Maven coordinates
                - if client_name == "java"                
                  %a.btn.btn-success{:href=>client_info.stable.download, :style => "width: 130px;"} 
                    %i.icon-download-alt
                    #{client_info.stable.version} Zip
                  .pull-right
                    .label.label-success
                      %i.icon-check-sign
                      Stable
                  %a.btn.btn-warning{:href=>client_info.unstable.download, :style => "width: 130px;"} 
                    %i.icon-download-alt
                    #{client_info.unstable.version} Zip
                  .pull-right
                    .label.label-warning
                      %i.icon-warning-sign
                      Unstable
                  %br
                  = partial( 'maven-coords-link.html.haml', {"artifactId" => client_info.maven_artifact_id, "modal_id" => "icr", "version_stable" => client_info.stable.version, "version_unstable" => client_info.unstable.version} )    
                - else
                  -# Otherwise just display a GitHub link
                  = partial( 'view-on-github-button.html.haml', {"repo" => client_info.github} )              
 
  .span3
    %h3 Hot Rod
    %p
      Hot Rod is a wire protocol that Infinispan clients use to talk to a remote grid.  It is a binary, platform-independent protocol that was developed in the open as a part of Infinispan.
    %p
      The Hot Rod
      %a{:href => "https://docs.jboss.org/author/display/ISPN/Hot+Rod+Protocol"} specification
      is available on-line, and several clients exist for this protocol.
    %hr
    %h3 Contributing Clients
    %p Want to contribute more clients for Hot Rod? Weâ€™d love you to do so!
    %i.icon-tag
    %a{:href => "https://docs.jboss.org/author/display/ISPN/Contributing+to+Infinispan"} Learn more about getting involved.
    %hr
    = partial("rightcol-docs.html.haml")
